SCRIPT EXPLANATIONS

dev:
  - Starts development server with HMR
  - Hot Module Replacement for instant updates

build:
  - Type checks with TypeScript (tsc)
  - Creates production build
  - Minifies and optimizes code

build:analyze:
  - Same as build but opens bundle analyzer
  - Visualize what's in your bundle
  - Identify large dependencies

preview:
  - Preview production build locally
  - Test before deploying

lint:
  - Check code for errors
  - ESLint with TypeScript rules
  - React-specific rules

lint:fix:
  - Auto-fix linting errors

format:
  - Format code with Prettier
  - Consistent code style

format:check:
  - Check if code is formatted
  - Good for CI/CD

type-check:
  - Run TypeScript compiler without emitting files
  - Catch type errors

test:
  - Run tests in watch mode
  - Re-runs on file changes

test:ui:
  - Run tests with Vitest UI
  - Visual test runner

test:coverage:
  - Generate coverage report
  - See what's tested

prepare:
  - Set up Husky git hooks
  - Runs automatically after npm install

HUSKY & LINT-STAGED SETUP

1. Install husky and lint-staged (already in devDependencies)

2. Initialize husky:
   npx husky install

3. Add pre-commit hook:
   npx husky add .husky/pre-commit "npx lint-staged"

4. Add pre-push hook (optional):
   npx husky add .husky/pre-push "npm run type-check && npm run test:coverage"

This ensures:
  - Code is linted and formatted before commit
  - Types are checked before push
  - Tests pass before push

RECOMMENDED NPM SCRIPTS FOR CI/CD

{
  "scripts": {
    "ci:install": "npm ci",
    "ci:lint": "npm run lint && npm run format:check",
    "ci:type-check": "npm run type-check",
    "ci:test": "npm run test:coverage",
    "ci:build": "npm run build",
    "ci": "npm run ci:lint && npm run ci:type-check && npm run ci:test && npm run ci:build"
  }
}

CI/CD Pipeline (GitHub Actions example):
  1. npm ci          (Clean install)
  2. npm run ci      (Lint, type-check, test, build)
  3. Upload artifacts
  4. Deploy

ENVIRONMENT VARIABLES

Create .env files:

.env.development:
  VITE_API_URL=http://localhost:5000
  VITE_APP_TITLE=My App (Dev)

.env.production:
  VITE_API_URL=https://api.example.com
  VITE_APP_TITLE=My App

Usage in code:
  const apiUrl = import.meta.env.VITE_API_URL;

PACKAGE.JSON BEST PRACTICES

1. Use exact versions in production
   - No ^ or ~ for critical dependencies
   - Ensures consistent builds

2. Use peerDependencies for libraries
   - Avoid version conflicts
   - Reduce bundle size

3. Use "type": "module"
   - Enable ESM
   - Modern JavaScript

4. Set "private": true
   - Prevent accidental publish to npm

5. Use npm ci in CI/CD
   - Faster and more reliable
   - Uses package-lock.json exactly
